article.headline: Vermont 68, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 61
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. -- Evan Fjeld scored 20 points to lead Vermont past Mount St. Mary's (Md.) in overtime, 69-61, on Wednesday night. The Catamounts (9-3) led 52-50 after a free throw from Fjeld with 25 seconds left in regulation. Shawn Atupem sent the game into overtime on a buzzer-beating layup. Vermont started the extra period on an 11-2 run and led by at least five points over the final 90 seconds. Matt Glass scored 13 and Joey Accaoui added 10 -- including six in overtime -- for the Catamounts. The Mountaineers (3-11), who have lost seven games in a row, were led by Julian Norfleet and Lamar Trice with 13 points each. Vermont dominated play on the inside, outrebounding the Mountaineers 41-34 and posting a 38-28 scoring edge on points in the paint. The Catamounts were 26 for 53 from the field (49.1 percent), while holding Mount St. Mary's to 38.2 percent shooting (26 of 68).
